message.en_US: Do you have the \c[3]\v[item.toggle-arcanelab-skill.name]\c[0] item?
[shakes head]
You'll need that to use the cheat codes since I have them set up as \c[3]custom skills\c[0].
The modding community provides one to everyone in the east room of the main hideout.
Go get it before we continue.
Welcome to my little testing area.
First, let's give you the cheats...

text.en_US: You now have access to the \i[element-neutral]\c[1]cheat codes\c[0] collection of skills.

message.en_US: Don't worry, that just means it works.
My script just needed to reboot you so it could get root access.
Look, did you want the codes or not?
You now have the codes. Equip them from that \c[3]custom skill menu\c[0].
Make sure you remember to turn on the \c[3]\v[item.toggle-arcanelab-skill.name]\c[0] item.
All cheat codes are available as \c[3]level 1 neutral arts\c[0], got it?
[nods]
See that other room over there?
[nods]
There is no way in. No doors or anything.
But we can walk through walls using the \c[1]NoClip\c[0] cheat.
It's a \c[3]level 1 neutral dash art\c[0] in the custom skill menu.
Now you will watch and meet me in the next room.
You use a \c[3]dash\c[0] to turn off \c[1]NoClip\c[0].
Now come over here so we can see the other codes.
Heh heh...\. Nice work.
The next cheat is called \c[1]cliff jump\c[0].
You can use it to climb any ledges like this one.
Now it's your turn. Use \c[1]cliff jump\c[0] to get up here.
Lea!
Not bad! That one is good for skipping annoying jump puzzles.
There are more codes included than just these. They are always going to be \c[3]level 1 neutral arts\c[0].
Although there is something important you need to know...
The game was never designed with these in mind. You can break it very easily if you are not careful.
Never leave a map in the middle of a scripted fight or puzzle sequence.
Doing that will cause the entire map to break. You should also make backup saves before using the cheats too much.
One other thing...\. We have never met.
If you break your game or get in trouble, don't come cry to me about it.
Our little meeting never happened, got it?
[nods]
Enjoy your new "skills"!\! Goodbye.
